{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/4-things-to-do-before-you-start-studying-nlp-f800c2a3c392", "time": 1683008436.355509, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/4-things-to-do-before-you-start-studying-nlp-f800c2a3c392/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "4 Things To Do Before You Start Studying NLP | by Ugo Loobuyck | Towards Data Science", "h1": "4 Things To Do Before You Start Studying NLP", "description": "Getting started in a new field isn\u2019t always easy when you don\u2019t have the right resources or are missing crucial information, even when this field is as fun as Natural Language Processing! I have been\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://medium.com/@mindfiresolutions.usa/python-7-important-reasons-why-you-should-use-python-5801a98a0d0b", "anchor_text": "this article", "paragraph_index": 2}], "all_paragraphs": ["Getting started in a new field isn\u2019t always easy when you don\u2019t have the right resources or are missing crucial information, even when this field is as fun as Natural Language Processing!", "I have been an NLP student for the past two years and there are a few things I wish I knew before I started my master\u2019s degree. In this post, I will tell you about the top 4 things that would have saved me a ton of time when I started studying NLP.", "Python is currently the most popular programming language for machine learning, AI and NLP. It essentially has access to a great number of useful libraries and is user-friendly, as explained in this article.", "You should train your basic text processing skills and practice Python functions like split(), lower(), etc. Knowing data structures (lists, dictionaries, sets) and ways to handle them is also essential (list slices, looping through dictionaries, the zip() and enumerate() functions).", "There are a handful of important Python libraries you should get acquainted with:", "Numpy, Pandas and Matplotlib are very popular on the machine learning side of NLP, and you will often encounter the following lines at the beginning of scripts:", "If you happen to already know the basics of Python programming as well as some of these libraries, you can start getting familiar with machine learning frameworks described in the following article.", "Mathematics are a core component of NLP and will accompany you on your journey to mastering this discipline. Even though you probably won\u2019t have to ever pull off insane calculations by hand to make your project work, understanding what\u2019s happening in the machine is a fundamental asset to develop your skills.", "As a beginner, here are the things you should get familiar with when delving into NLP:", "The more you know about basic maths, the easier it will be for you to grasp core NLP concepts. But enough about maths!", "As a future NLP master, it will happen quite often that you need to create a new, clean programming environment for a new project. But as a beginner, setting up your very first project can be made much simpler by using the following tools:", "Perhaps this piece of advice is more adapted for intermediate learners who already have some experience or knowledge of the field.", "This was for me the most overwhelming aspect of NLP, since I had never read a single scientific paper before and was unaware of the valuable takeaways contained in each of them. At the end of the day, I wish I had started reading papers, and here is why:", "I honestly wish I had these tips in hand when I started learning NLP and machine learning.", "Learning Python and maths basics will help you climb that learning curve, setting a good working environment will save you a ton of time on file and package management, and reading research papers will inform you on what\u2019s new.", "Thank you for reading, I sincerely hope that these tips will save you some time and trouble when learning NLP. Don\u2019t hesitate to leave feedback and tell me about what you wish you knew when you started learning NLP and machine learni